cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Mathematics of Music — machine-checked notes & Lean library"
message: "If you use this work, please cite it. Each released note also carries its own Zenodo DOI; prefer the specific note's DOI."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Marín"
    given-names: "Carles"
    email: "karlesmarin@gmail.com"
    affiliation: "Independent researcher"
abstract: >-
  Honest, machine-checked results in mathematical music theory: focused research
  notes backed by Lean 4 / Mathlib formalizations (sorry-free, axiom-clean) and
  reproducible Sage/GAP witnesses. Prepared with the assistance of an AI system
  (Claude, Anthropic); the mathematics is classical and the scope of each note is
  stated explicitly.
keywords:
  - mathematical music theory
  - pitch-class set theory
  - neo-Riemannian theory
  - Lean 4
  - formalization of mathematics
license: Apache-2.0
version: "3.0.0"
doi: 10.5281/zenodo.20820962
date-released: 2026-06-25
